ersion interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`)\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: type Interface interface {\n133: \tAgentRuntimes() AgentRuntimeInformer\n134: \tCodeInterpreters() CodeInterpreterInformer\n135: }\n136: ```\n137: \n138: ### Per-type informers (`.../runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`)\n139: \n140: Example (`AgentRuntimeInformer`):\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: type AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n144: \tInformer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n145: \tLister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n146: }\n147: ```\n148: \n149: Also provides `NewAgentRuntimeInformer`, `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer`, and analogous constructors for CodeInterpreter.\n150: \n151: ### Generic resource routing (`informers/externalversions/generic.go`)\n152: \n153: `ForResource` switches on:\n154: \n155: - `v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\")` → `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n156: - `...WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\")` → `...CodeInterpreters().Informer()`\n157: \n158: ### `internalinterfaces` (`informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`)\n159: \n160: ```go\n161: type NewInformerFunc func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n162: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n163: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n164: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n165: }\n166: type TweakListOptionsFunc func(*metav1.ListOptions)\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Listers (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n172: \n173: ### `AgentRuntimeLister` / `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` (`agentruntime.go`)\n174: \n175: ```go\n176: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n177: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n178: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n179: \tAgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n180: }\n181: \n182: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n183: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n184: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n185: \tAgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: `NewAgentRuntimeLister` uses `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()`.\n190: \n191: ### `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` (`codeinterpreter.go`)\n192: \n193: Same pattern for `CodeInterpreter`; `NewCodeInterpreterLister` uses `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`.\n194: \n195: ### Expansion (`expansion_generated.go`)\n196: \n197: Empty expansion interfaces for listers and namespace listers (all four types).\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## Fake clientset (`clientset/versioned/fake/`)\n202: \n203: | File | Role |\n204: |------|------|\n205: | `clientset_generated.go` | `NewSimpleClientset`, `NewClientset` — in-memory fake `Clientset` |\n206: | `register.go` | Scheme registration for fakes |\n207: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ## File index (all paths under `client-go/`)\n212: \n213: | Path | Role |\n214: |------|------|\n215: | `clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n216: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n217: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n218: | `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n219: | `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n220: | `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n221: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n222: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n223: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n224: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n225: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n226: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n227: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n228: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n229: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n230: | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n231: | `informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n232: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n233: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n234: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n235: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n236: | `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Small factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n237: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n238: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n239: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n240: \n241: **Regeneration:** `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` (`k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1, `--with-watch`, output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`).\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ## Error Handling\n246: \n247: ### Client Errors\n248: \n249: | Error Type | Description | Handling |\n250: |------------|-------------|----------|\n251: | `IsAlreadyExists()` | Resource already exists (Create) | Retry with different name or GET existing |\n252: | `IsNotFound()` | Resource does not exist (Get/Update/Delete) | Check if needs Create first |\n253: | `IsConflict()` | Resource version mismatch (Update) | Fetch latest and retry |\n254: | `IsTimeout()` | Operation timed out | Retry with exponential backoff |\n255: | `IsServerTimeout()` | Server returned 504 | Retry |\n256: | `IsBadRequest()` | Invalid request body | Fix validation before retry |\n257: \n258: ### Informer Errors\n259: \n260: | Scenario | Behavior |\n261: |----------|----------|\n262: | List/Watch failure | Log error, re-queue with backoff |\n263: | Cache sync failure | `WaitForCacheSync` returns false |\n264: | Graceful shutdown | `Shutdown()` stops all informers |\n265: \n266: ### Common Patterns\n267: \n268: ```go\n269: // Retry with backoff\n270: func withRetry(fn func() error) error {\n271:     var lastErr error\n272:     for i := 0; i < 3; i++ {\n273:         if err := fn(); err != nil {\n274:             if errors.IsRetryable(err) {\n275:                 lastErr = err\n276:                 time.Sleep(time.Duration(i+1) * time.Second)\n277:                 continue\n278:             }\n279:             return err\n280:         }\n281:         return nil\n282:     }\n283:     return lastErr\n284: }\n285: \n286: // Handle conflict\n287: func updateWithRetry(ctx context.Context, client typedInterface, name string, updateFunc func(*T) *T) (*T, error) {\n288:     for {\n289:         current, err := client.Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n290:         if err != nil {\n291:             return nil, err\n292:         }\n293:         updated := updateFunc(current)\n294:         result, err := client.Update(ctx, updated, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n295:         if errors.IsConflict(err) {\n296:             continue // retry with fresh version\n297:         }\n298:         return result, err\n299:     }\n300: }\n301: ```\n302: \n303: ---\n304: \n305: ## Testing Strategy\n306: \n307: ### Unit Tests\n308: \n309: | Component | Test Approach |\n310: |-----------|----------------|\n311: | Typed clients | Mock REST interface, verify request paths |\n312: | Listers | Populate indexer, verify List/Get methods |\n313: | Informers | Use fake client, verify event handlers |\n314: | Fake clients | Verify method signatures match interfaces |\n315: \n316: ### Fake Client Usage\n317: \n318: ```go\n319: import (\n320:     \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n321:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/fake\"\n322: )\n323: \n324: func TestAgentRuntimeController(t *testing.T) {\n325:     // Create fake clients\n326:     k8s := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n327:     agentcube := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n328:     \n329:     // Pre-populate resources\n330:     agentcube.AgentRuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(ctx, &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n331:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"test-runtime\"},\n332:         Spec:       runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{...},\n333:     }, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n334:     \n335:     // Test controller logic\n336:     controller := NewController(k8s, agentcube)\n337:     // ... assertions\n338: }\n339: ```\n340: \n341: ### Integration Tests\n342: \n343: | Test Type | Environment | Notes |\n344: |-----------|-------------|-------|\n345: | E2E | Kind cluster with CRDs installed | Use envtest or actual cluster |\n346: | Contract | Verify generated code matches API spec | Compare against handwritten stubs |\n347: \n348: ### Test Helpers\n349: \n350: | Function | Purpose |\n351: |----------|---------|\n352: | `NewFakeClientset()` | Creates in-memory clientset |\n353: | `NewFakeRuntimeClient()` | Typed runtime client |\n354: | `NewFakeInformer()` | Pre-populated informer |\n355: \n356: ---\n357: \n358: ## Architecture\n359: \n360: ### Component Relationships\n361: \n362: ```\n363: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n364: │                        Clientset                             │\n365: │  ┌─────────────────┐    ┌────────────────────────────────┐ │\n366: │  │ DiscoveryClient │    │   RuntimeV1alpha1Client        │ │\n367: │  └─────────────────┘    │  ┌──────────┐  ┌─────────────┐ │ │\n368: │                         │  │AgentRun- │  │CodeInterpr- │ │ │\n369: │                         │  │times     │  │eter        │ │ │\n370: │                         │  └──────────┘  └─────────────┘ │ │\n371: │                         └────────────────────────────────┘ │\n372: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n373:                               │\n374:          ┌────────────────────┼────────────────────┐\n375:          ▼                    ▼                    ▼\n376: ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n377: │ SharedInformer  │  │   Listers   │  │   Controllers    │\n378: │ Factory         │  │             │  │   (workloadmgr)  │\n379: │ ┌─────────────┐ │  │ ┌─────────┐ │  └──────────────────┘\n380: │ │AgentRuntime │ │  │ │AgentRun-│ │\n381: │ │Informer     │ │  │ │times    │ │\n382: │ └─────────────┘ │  │ │Lister   │ │\n383: │ ┌─────────────┐ │  │ └─────────┘ │  ┌──────────────────┐\n384: │ │CodeInterp   │ │  │ ┌─────────┐ │  │   Router        │\n385: │ │Informer     │ │  │ │CodeIn-  │ │  └──────────────────┘\n386: │ └─────────────┘ │  │ │terpreter│ │\n387: └─────────────────┘  │ │Lister   │ │\n388:                       │ └─────────┘ │\n389:                       └─────────────┘\n390: ```\n391: \n392: ### Data Flow\n393: \n394: 1. **Controller** creates/updates CR objects via typed client\n395: 2. **Clientset** sends REST requests to API server\n396: 3. **Informer** watches for changes, populates local cache\n397: 4. **Lister** provides cached lookups without API server calls\n398: 5. **Status subresource** allows separate status updates\n\n(End of file - total 398 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# client-go library\n\nGenerated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` 